Loop iter (2026-05-25): found the 4TH and deepest layer of the codesearch-empty bug + fixed it (rs-plugkit 4689b7d). Full stack of causes, each hidden behind the last: (1) ROUTING — recall/codesearch verbs routed to legacy libsql instead of file-vec (fixed 1d21ac7). (2) BACKEND-SPLIT — code_index wrote libsql but codesearch reads file-vec (fixed e17696d: dual-write + autobuild). (3) BUILD-PROVENANCE — rust-cache constant key shipped stale wasm so e17696d wasn't in the binary (fixed 0905378: rm wasm + cargo clean -p before build). (4) LIBSQL-GATE — even with a fresh binary, code_index::index() returned early on 'if Err(ensure_schema) return' because libsql/wasi schema init fails in this wasm (rs-learn.db wasi-shim fragility), aborting before any file-vec write. Fixed 4689b7d: ensure_schema best-effort, file-vec dual-write always runs, added entry log. VALIDATION METHOD that cracked it: 0.1.563 built from 09053784 (the provenance-fix commit) so the binary WAS fresh+contained e17696d, yet codesearch still {data:[]} in 180ms with ZERO code_index log -> the index fn itself was aborting silently -> read index() entry -> ensure_schema early-return. LESSON: when a fix is confirmed-in-binary but still no-ops, the called function may be failing silently before the fixed code; add an entry log and read the function's first lines. Validate on next cascade > 0.1.563. Validated live on 0.1.563: slug-alias + memorize-prune work.